properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued February 1 at 3:59PM AKST until February 2 at 5:00PM AKST by NWS Anchorage, AK
properties.description:
* WHAT...Blowing snow expected. Total snow accumulations of up to
6 inches. Winds gusting as high as 35 mph will reduce
visibilities to one half mile or less.

* WHERE...Along the Coast of the Kuskokwim Delta.

* WHEN...From 3 AM to 5 PM AKST Sunday.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions. Areas of blowing
snow could significantly reduce visibility.
properties.instruction:
for blowing snow means that visibilities will be limited due to
strong winds blowing snow around. Use caution when traveling,
especially in open areas.

Slow down and use caution while traveling.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 3 AM TO 5 PM AKST SUNDAY ALONG THE COAST
